<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4274] RS should periodically ping its HLog pipeline even if no writes are arriving</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4274</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If you restart HDFS underneath HBase, when HBase isn&apos;t taking any write load, the region servers won&apos;t &quot;notice&quot; that there&apos;s any problem until the next time they take a write, at which point they will abort (because the pipeline is gone from beneath them). It would be better if they wrote some garbage to their HLog once every few seconds as a sort of keepalive, so they will aggressively abort as soon as there&apos;s an issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12520521">HBASE-4274</key>
            <summary>RS should periodically ping its HLog pipeline even if no writes are arriving</summary>
