                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13092698" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2011 08:30:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Doesn&apos;t &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4222&quot; title=&quot;Make HLog more resilient to write pipeline failures&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4222&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4222&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; already address this? It takes a different approach, and arguably a better one. No need to abort if a new HLog pipeline can be established.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13093327" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 30 Aug 2011 00:12:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In general we should opt for strategies that allow the RS to ride over short DFS interruptions, such as a rolling restart of DNs, or a switch reload or failover, or similar. So I lean toward -1 changes that make the RS more aggressive about terminating in such situations as long as we also reason carefully about (avoiding) data loss.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13129147" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Mon, 17 Oct 2011 20:28:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Gary has addressed rolling restart of DNs.&lt;br/&gt;
Can we move this issue to 0.94 ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13134804" author="stack" created="Tue, 25 Oct 2011 07:20:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Moving out of 0.92.  This does not seem to be a critical 0.92 issue any more given Gary work.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13234512" author="lhofhansl" created="Wed, 21 Mar 2012 17:06:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No movement, removing from 0.92.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13549854" author="stack" created="Thu, 10 Jan 2013 18:09:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Marking down to major and moving out of 0.96.  Bring back in if folks want RS to die quickly when HDFS goes out from under HBase (It does seem like general tendency though is to go the other direction, and try and ride over an HDFS outage if possible).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15671586" author="stack" created="Wed, 16 Nov 2016 20:49:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rather than ping so we can crash closer to the removal of HDFS, instead try and ride over a restart... as in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4222&quot; title=&quot;Make HLog more resilient to write pipeline failures&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-4222&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-4222&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1401&quot; title=&quot;close HLog (and open new one) if there hasnt been edits in N minutes/hours&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1401&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1401&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is related in that forces a roll on a period whether writes or not.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Resolving as won&apos;t do.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
